SIMPLE: homespun
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homespun
<hw>Home"spun</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Spun or
wrought at home; of domestic manufacture; coarse; plain.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Homespun</xex> country garbs.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W.
Irving.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Plain in manner or style; not elegant; rude;
coarse.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Our <xex>homespun</xex> English proverb.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Dryden.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Our <xex>homespun</xex> authors.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Addison.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homespun</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Homespun
<hw>Home"spun</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Cloth made at home;
<as>as, he was dressed in <ex>homespun</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An unpolished, rustic person.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homestall</ent>⟦br⟧
